						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the ruined temple of Lakshmīnārāyaṇasvāmi.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1188, Prabhava Vaiśākha, śu. 13, Friday, corresponding to 1267 A.D., April 8.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Contains verses in praise of a chief named Janārdana and his minister Dēvaya born in the Kauśika-gōtra. Further it records the consecration of the temple Lakshmīnārāyaṇa at Tāḷḷapalli.</p>						

						</summary>
